stylometry: Producing or ordering costs tradeoff would be sending it straight to the company that wants it or warehouse for holding which in turn is it's own - holding cost -  which means dilemma for decisions because the product isn't being sold it is being stored. Which a lot can be a tough decision because you must decide whether to produce that product in the first place - a lot to do with demand here, and the cycle of how long it will be held. There are tradeoffs within holding costs too because one warehouse can send it to another. When the ultimate goal is to get that product out there and ordered or sold in (another trade-off) a store, or other company, etc. Which is going to ultimately maximize a company's profit? - is what must be decided.
